she solved Einstein's maths problem that the
law of their maths -- this conservation of energy --
was only an approximation of a deeper law -- the law of least work, or least effort

this is *wuwei*

that the shortest causal path
  the minimum transformation
between any two points
within this warped fabric of spacetime

is the path of least effort or work

the idea here
that Emmy started

was that what we percieve to be
the shortest path between to things -- between what we want and what we are --

that this isn't always what we might think
that there are underlying symmetries that must be preserved

but sometimes what appears the easiest path
is not

and while this seems obvious when said this way
the very idea that this "sometimes the apparently easiest path isn't the easiest"

is novel
